snippet.textDisplay: Indeed, sars-cov-2 seems not to accumulate too many mutations, despite the fact that its an RNA virus. Im currently working on covid19 phylogenetics, and the first time i generated a multiple sequence alignment of covid19 genomes, i couldnt help noticing how little mutations there were (and considering some of them are sequencing errors, they should actually be even less).
